## range() function

Generate an iterable range

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
declare function range(start: string | number, end: string | number): never[] | {
    start: string | number;
    end: string | number;
};
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  start | string \| number | lower limit of range |
|  end | string \| number | upper limit of range |

<b>Returns:</b>

never\[\] \| { start: string \| number; end: string \| number; }

## Example

if (n in range(1, 20)) doStuff();
